div.div:
Project Architecture
This architecture diagram represents a system that integrates a knowledge engine, JupyterHub, and a remote graph database to provide users with a virtual thermostat and access to knowledge bases. The system uses Docker containers, REST, knowledge interactions, and SPARQL to facilitate communication between its various components. The JupyterHub container manages user access and provides each user with a set of notebooks, including an API and UI for the virtual thermostat and several knowledge base notebooks. The knowledge base notebooks serve as UI, storage, and monitoring tools, allowing users to print graphs and query the graph database.
